Package io.deepstream

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AnonymousRecordNameChangedListener
    A listener that notifies the user whenever AnonymousRecord.setName(String) is called
    ConnectionStateListener
    A listener that will be notified whenever the ConnectionState changes.
    DeepstreamRuntimeErrorHandler
    The expectations would be for java clients to implement this and add it via the *setDeepstreamRuntimeErrorHandler* handler in order to catch all runtime errors that can occur without requiring to listening to it on seperate threads.
    EventListener
    An EventListener is notified whenever it is triggered locally or remotely.
    ListChangedListener
    List change callbacks TODO: Split these for performance reasons?
    ListenListener
    An interface that notifies whenever a pattern match has been found TODO: Entirely changes with new listener functionality
    RecordChangedCallback
    Record data changed listener, used to be notified whenever the record data has been modified either locally or remotely.
    RecordEventsListener
    Record state changed listener, used to be notified whenever the record state has occurred
    RecordMergeStrategy
    Allows users to reconcile record versions if the data is not correctly in sync ( out of sync record versions )
    RpcRequestedListener
    Listener for any rpc requests recieved from the server
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnonymousRecord
    An AnonymousRecord is a record without a predefined name.

    deepstream.io java client
    DeepstreamError  
    EventHandler  
    InvalidDeepstreamConfig  
    List
    A List is a specialised Record that contains an Array of recordNames and provides a number of convinience methods for interacting with them.
    LoginResult
    A result of a login, indicating if it was successful or not and associated data.
    Record
    This class represents a single record - an observable dataset returned by RecordHandler.getRecord(String)

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AnonymousRecordUninitialized
    An exception that is thrown if you try to do a AnonymousRecord.discard() or AnonymousRecord.delete() before a record has been set via AnonymousRecord.setName(String)
    DeepstreamException
    A DeepstreamException is a RuntimeException since they mostly occur when recieving an out of sync message from the server, or if an Ack has timed out.
    DeepstreamLoginException
    A DeepstreamLoginException occurs if you login to a connection that was forcefully closed due to Event.UNAUTHENTICATED_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT or if the login attempts exceed the maximum Event.TOO_MANY_AUTH_ATTEMPTS
    DeepstreamRecordDestroyedException
    Called whenever you try to perform an action on a record that has been discarded/deleted.
    RecordMergeStrategyException
    Thrown when a version conflict occurs, and is only exposed to the client via RecordEventsListener.onError(String, Event, String)
